        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 4:53PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 453 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Brazos Bend State Park, or 14 miles north of West Columbia, moving
east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brazos Bend State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
